  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And so he-- just in the coffee break or the lunch break-- told-- told us that-- how to get in touch with the hard to find communist movement in-- in-- in fascist countries, in bad countries, because he knew that they were the best country-- and they never made-- any-- what you call it-- any secret of it.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in-- in a lecture room, he couldn't come out open, but he told us personally, like in Hungary, because there, the communist were really in-- behind the skirts of Social Democratic Party.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were actually built in, you see?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That-- that-- that's how they operated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and then he told us that this kinds of tricks, you see-- how-- how to find him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so-- and sure enough, when we landed-- I landed in-- in the Hungary then-- and the people, my-- my contacts-- my first contacts were-- were Social Democrats.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they already had contact with the-- the British Labor Party through the British embassy in-- in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well then-- then-- we were-- we were trained in-- in England before we go-- before we go any further-- so this intelligence.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Courses were-- were-- were one after the other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The-- the-- the-- the most amazing things that they did they taught us.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And just, we inject when I came back from the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so I had to be careful for about two years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I was my own-- own-- own-- own prisoner.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I was my own prisoner, because I-- I was tempted-- I was tempted to do things that it was absolutely out.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Look, I could open and safes and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we were trained so better-- the chief-- [LAUGHS] three-- they had three safe crackers in-- in England who were in jail.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
